cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.MS 

The paper deals with optimization methods for machine learning applications, specifically for classification problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of GPUs for acceleration, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification problems, which could potentially place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of Newton-type methods and Alternating Direction of Method Multipliers (ADMM) suggests a possible fit with cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
